statement:
Let

\begin{align*}A = \begin{bmatrix}
1 & 3 \\ 3 & 8
\end{bmatrix}
\qquad 
B = \begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0 & -1 \\ -3 & 1 & 0
\end{bmatrix}\end{align*}

Calculate the following whenever defined. Otherwise state
\textbf{undefined} and include a brief explanation.

$\displaystyle AB$

sols:
Since \emph{A} is \textbf{2}x2 matrix and \emph{B} is a 2x\textbf{3}
matrix, the resulting matrix \emph{AB} will be \textbf{2}x\textbf{3}.

Performing the matrix multiplication, we get

\begin{align*}
AB &= \begin{bmatrix}
1 & 3 \\ 3 & 8
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0 & -1 \\ -3 & 1 & 0
\end{bmatrix}\\
&= 
\begin{bmatrix}
(1)(1) + (3)(-3) & (1)(0) + (3)(1) & (1)(-1) + (3)(0) \\ (3)(1) + (8)(-3) & (3)(0) + (8)(1) & (3)(-1)  + (8)(0)
\end{bmatrix}\\
&= 
\begin{bmatrix}
-8 & 3 & -1 \\ -21 & 8 & -3
\end{bmatrix}\end{align*}
